Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
3515 Dawson Road is a 134,475± s.f. industrial complex on 8.3± acres. It features a main plant of 112,544 s.f. with multiple overhead cranes from five (5) tons up to thirty (30) tons. The hook heights range from 15' to 28'. The reported electrical service is 480V, 3 Phase, 3,000 Amps.

The main plant has two office areas, a large breakroom and restrooms. Several oversized overhead doors are located throughout.

Other structures on site include administrative offices of 6,931 s.f. This freestanding office building has numerous private offices, an open area for cubicles and two conference rooms.

A crane-served shop/warehouse of 12,600 s.f. is located east of the main plant. It measures 70’ x 180’ and has three (3) 5 ton cranes and three (3) drive-in doors. A 2,400 s.f. shipping/receiving warehouse is near the main entrance, just south of the main plant. It has a 12’ x 10’ drive-in door on the north end facing the main plant.
